node.text: We’re at home with Resident @chetnamakan, and today she’s making a recipe from her new cookbook, ‘Chetna’s 30 Minute Indian’, Sour & Spicy Potatoes (Alu Chaat)! Grab the full recipe to make for yourself at the link in bio. #f52community

node.title: Sour & Spicy Potatoes (Alu Chaat) with Chetna Makan - At Home With Us

node.text: @nappyfriiedchicken is back, back again, and today he’s whipping up one of his favorite snacks, French Onion Labneh with Homemade Chips! Life tip: bring this to your next cookout or picnic, and everyone will thank you for it. Get the recipe at the link in bio. #f52community

node.title: French Onion Labneh with Homemade Chips with Romel Bruno - At Home With Us

node.text: Today we’re hanging out with @grossypelosi in his Brooklyn kitchen, making a dessert he ate all summer as a child: his Grandma’s Italian cream-filled sponge cake! Plus, as a treat, he’s showing three different ways you can decorate the top (a big dollop of whipped cream is required for all!). Grab the full recipe at the link in bio. #f52community

node.title: Grandma’s Italian Sponge Cake with Dan Pelosi - At Home With Us

node.text: We're back in @amandahesser's kitchen, and today, she's making fall-off-the-bone ribs that are sure to score serious points at your next barbeque. They get slathered in a rub mixture of sea salt, paprika, ground coffee beans, and peppercorns, then slow-cooked for 7 hours (for maximum flavor!). Grab Resident @ladyandpups's recipe for Coffee-Crusted Barbecue Beef Ribs at the link in bio. #f52community

node.title: Coffee-Crusted Barbecue Beef Ribs - Amanda Messes Up in the Kitchen

node.text: Meet your new favorite pasta dish: @mateo.zielonka's fennel, shallot, and capers chitarra recipe! From his book "Pasta Man" this dish is all about fresh flavors with homemade semolina pasta, shallots, fennel, capers, and served with plenty of nutritional yeast. Grab the recipe at the link in bio. #f52community

node.text: It’s Saturday, and we recommend making Savour’s Simple Summer Peach Cake just like @amandahesser did! It’s simple, perfect for a barbecue (or picnic), and a great way to use up ripe seasonal peaches (well, if you haven’t snacked on all of them first!). Grab the full recipe at the link in bio. #f52community

node.title: Simple Summer Peach Cake - Amanda Messes Up in the Kitchen

node.text: Chickpeas and beets are two of Resident @amychaplin’s favorite ingredients, so today, we’re in her home kitchen making her recipe for Beet-Chickpea Cakes With Tzatziki! Eat them warm (or at room temperature!) on their own, pair them with pita and vegetables, and of course, a generous spoonful of tzatziki. Snag the recipe at the link in bio. #f52community

node.title: Beet-Chickpea Cakes with Amy Chaplin - At Home With Us

node.text: We’re at home with Resident @chetnamakan, and today she’s making a recipe from her new cookbook, ‘Chetna’s 30 Minute Indian’, Sour & Spicy Potatoes (Alu Chaat)! Grab the full recipe to make for yourself at the link in bio. #f52community

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food52 in Food52 with @carolinagelen. May be an image of dessert and indoor.

node.text: Resident @carolinagelen is on a *roll* with summer creations, and her latest is a light, not-too-sweet, raspberry dessert! The fluffy sponge cake is filled with fresh raspberries (instead of the typical raspberry jam) and white chocolate whipped cream (it's more stable than regular whipped cream). Grab her Raspberry Cake Roll recipe at the link in bio. #f52community

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food52 in Food52 with @melinahammer. May be an image of tomato and indoor.

node.text: ✨ Peak-ripe produce ✨ courtesy of Resident @melinahammer. In her latest, tomatoes and cucumbers are the stars of the show, but it's the briny capers (which puff into a crunchy, sublime topping after a few minutes on a hot skillet) that steal the show. Get the recipe at the link in our bio. #f52community

node.text: @nappyfriiedchicken is back, back again, and today he’s whipping up one of his favorite snacks, French Onion Labneh with Homemade Chips! Life tip: bring this to your next cookout or picnic, and everyone will thank you for it. Get the recipe at the link in bio. #f52community

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food52 in Food52 with @purple_turnips. May be an image of 1 person and dessert.

node.text: Basbousa slowly became one of @purple_turnips' favorite desserts, and we can see why! It's super-satisfying (but still light enough that you'll have room for seconds), drizzled with a sweet syrup, comes together in one bowl, and looks like a work of art when finished. Grab her Basbousa recipe at the link in bio. 📸: @tymecham

node.text: It's time for a midweek butter break! With the help of this Japanese Butter Knife, you'll have spreadable butter straight from the fridge whenever you want it! Head to the link in ourbio to shop for yours. 📸: @rockyluten

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food52 in Food52 with @feastwithsafiya. May be an image of biryani.

node.text: Continuing the tradition passed on from her Ammi, for @feastwithsafiya, Mutton Biryani is the perfect way to celebrate Eid al-Adha. Get the full recipe details on her page. #f52community #f52grams

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food52 in Food52 with @woon.heng. May be an image of food.

node.text: This recipe for Tofu Char Siu is @woon.heng's favorite way to eat tofu, so you know it has to be good! Best served with a side of flavored rice and chile sauce, it makes for an effortless meal that combines crispy tofu and a savory sauce. Try it for yourself by clicking the link in our bio. #f52community

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food52 in Food52 with @emmalaperruque. May be an image of food.

node.text: Three words: Buttery Balsamic Chicken! These are the latest from @emmalaperruque for Big Little Recipes, and the recipe uses balsamic not one, not two, but three different ways (a saltwater marinade, a sauce, and a fresh drizzle at the end). Try them out for yourself at the link in bio. 📸: @tymecham #f52community
